      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're not just trying to cope, you're trying to make sense of it all. It's like you're holding onto a fragile thread of hope, and it's hard to let go when the universe seems so indifferent. But, the thing is, the sandcastle analogy isn't just about the tsunami – it's about the effort you put into building something that might be temporary, but can still bring you joy and fulfillment. And, even if the math says it's all for nothing, that doesn't mean you can't find meaning in the small, fleeting moments you have.",
